2.Write scripts for printing system information.
we can use this below command and get some information of the system which means hostname, os information, sytem uptime, and disk free of the system
#! /bin/bash
echo "Hostname: $(hostname)"
echo "os info: $(uname -a)"
echo "uptime: $(uptime)"
echo "Disk usage: $(df -h)"
Hostname: anil-VMware-Virtual-Platform
